{"view":"article","slug":"big-l4e","category":"Big","subcategory":null,"topDir":"Big","title":{"en":"Big L4E Method (Last Four Edges)"},"content":{"en":"<p><a id=\"_Hlk505002238\"></a><a id=\"_Hlk514224610\"></a><strong>Big L4E Method (Last Four Edges)</strong></p><p><strong>高阶魔方后四棱方法</strong></p><p><strong>Restore Centers Before L4E</strong></p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image2.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><ol><li>Align top slice with second slice</li><li>Align bottom slice with penultimate slice </li><li>Align the remaining centers</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><p><span class=\"alg-chip\" data-alg=\"Uw' Dw2 3Uw'\">Uw' Dw2 3Uw'</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><strong>L4E First Edge Method</strong></p><p>Generally, find edge that have a bar or checker then use <strong>M' U2 M</strong>,<strong> </strong>slice-flip-slice method or 3-cycle method to solve this entire first edge (better look-ahead and reducing rotation), then solve the remaining edges. For terrible L4E (no bar or checker), use <strong>M' U2 M</strong> to create good L4E. </p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image4.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td><td></td><td><p><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image6.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Entire first edge</strong></p></td><td></td><td><p><strong>Entire L4E</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>Bar Examples</strong></p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>Checker Examples</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image8.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image10.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image12.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image14.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><strong>L4E Reduction Method</strong></p><p>For 7x7 cube terrible L4E, solve <strong>inner L4E</strong> and then the <strong>entire L4E</strong> just like solving 5x5 L4E twice.</p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image16.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td><td></td><td><p><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image6.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Inner L4E</strong></p></td><td></td><td><p><strong>Entire L4E</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><strong>Cycle Tip</strong></p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image18.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>× R U' R' 3Uw </strong>→ white-green edge not connected</p><p><strong>√ F R' F' R 3Uw </strong>→ white-green edge connected</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><strong>Big Cube L4E Algorithms</strong></p><p><strong>[Flip]</strong> denotes flip algorithm <strong>U' R' U R' F R F'. </strong>Conjugate <strong>A: B = A B A'.</strong></p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\"></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>6x6</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image20.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image22.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image24.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><img src=\"/stats/alg/media/big-l4e/en/image26.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"asyn